HEADWORD: Hyperinosis
<hw>Hy`per*i*no"sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>"ype`r</grk> over + <?/, <?/, strength, fiber.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A condition of the blood, characterized by an
abnormally large amount of fibrin, as in many inflammatory
diseases.</def>⟦br⟧
